Catholics don’t eat meat on Fridays or during lent. 

Numerous monastic orders have refrained from eating meat. 

Quakers and Seventh-Day Adventists are often vegetarian or #vegan.

Killing animals for food is needless. 

Avoiding meat is as simple as going to a different aisle in the grocery store.

So, should #Catholics be #vegan?
